  <span class="meta-name">Data Availability</span>
  <span class="meta-value">Our minimal data set can be found in the supplementary information. The data from which they were derived are publicly available: CHIRPS data can be found at 
   <span ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://chg.ucsb.edu/data/chirps/" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://chg.ucsb.edu/data/chirps/</span> Terrestrial Ecoregions of the World data can be found at 
   <span ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.worldwildlife.org/publications/terrestrial-ecoregions-of-the-world" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://www.worldwildlife.org/publications/terrestrial-ecoregions-of-the-world</span> Biodiversity Hotspots data can be found at 
   <span ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.cepf.net/resources/hotspots/Pages/default.aspx" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://www.cepf.net/resources/hotspots/Pages/default.aspx</span> Gridded Population of the World data can be found at 
   <span ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/data/collection/gpw-v3" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/data/collection/gpw-v3</span> Anthromes data can be found at 
   <span ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://ecotope.org/anthromes/data/" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://ecotope.org/anthromes/data/</span>
